    {
      "id": "4aa76514-1a3b-47bc-87b5-e29ab11e09e5",
      "type": "description",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Soit $f$ la fonction $2\\pi$-périodique telle que :\n$\\forall\\ x \\in {[-\\pi,\\pi[},\\ f(x) = e^x$.",
        "html": "<p>Soit <span class=\"math inline\">\\(f\\)</span> la fonction <span class=\"math inline\">\\(2\\pi\\)</span>-périodique telle que : <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\forall\\ x \\in {[-\\pi,\\pi[},\\ f(x) = e^x\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "eb3fbb32-da82-4cae-8f46-39f07dc62751",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Chercher le développement en série de Fourier de $f$.",
        "html": "<p>Chercher le développement en série de Fourier de <span class=\"math inline\">\\(f\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "ad0766b2-690b-4125-b961-f1686ddb40b2",
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": {
        "latex": "$a_0 = \\frac{2\\sh\\pi}\\pi$,\n             $a_n = \\frac{2(-1)^n\\sh\\pi}{\\pi(1+n^2)}$, $b_n = -na_n$.",
        "html": "<p><span class=\"math inline\">\\(a_0 = \\frac{2\\sh\\pi}\\pi\\)</span>, <span class=\"math inline\">\\(a_n = \\frac{2(-1)^n\\sh\\pi}{\\pi(1+n^2)}\\)</span>, <span class=\"math inline\">\\(b_n = -na_n\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "82c441fc-eacc-48d0-9f44-be0b6d8f1868",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "En déduire les sommes des séries :\n    $S = \\sum_{n=1}^\\infty \\frac1{n^2+1}$ et\n    $S' = \\sum_{n=1}^\\infty \\frac{(-1)^n}{n^2+1}$.",
        "html": "<p>En déduire les sommes des séries : <span class=\"math inline\">\\(S = \\sum_{n=1}^\\infty \\frac1{n^2+1}\\)</span> et <span class=\"math inline\">\\(S&#39; = \\sum_{n=1}^\\infty \\frac{(-1)^n}{n^2+1}\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "f6621d69-bb2c-4ec2-8100-82e5da53db5a",
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": {
        "latex": "$S = \\frac{\\pi-\\tanh\\pi}{2\\tanh\\pi}$,\n             $S' = \\frac{\\pi-\\sh\\pi}{2\\sh\\pi}$.",
        "html": "<p><span class=\"math inline\">\\(S = \\frac{\\pi-\\tanh\\pi}{2\\tanh\\pi}\\)</span>, <span class=\"math inline\">\\(S&#39; = \\frac{\\pi-\\sh\\pi}{2\\sh\\pi}\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    }
  ]
